MorphSwitchArea.Notes: If the player stays inside this area and fulfills the specified conditions (Obj_arg0), it will activate its SW_A switch. If the player leaves the area again or the condition is not met anymore, the switch will be deactivated again. If Obj_arg0 is set to 1, it will check if the player is "in rush". This refers to the state where the player is bound to another object, for example Fluzzard, Rock Mushroom's rolling rock, the Star Ball and more.

Obj_arg0.Name: Condition
Obj_arg0.Description: The required power-up state condition to activate the switch.

SW_A.Description: Gets activated or deactivated whether the specified condition is fulfilled or not.

PlaneCollisionArea.Notes: An area that extends the player's sensor range to detect items. This allows the player to collect an item while they stand closely behind or in front of it. This depends on the camera's view direction.

PlayerSideRetainOffArea.Notes: An area that adjusts the player's movement direction all the time. Usually, when a camera change occurs, the player will keep walking into the direction the stick was held before the camera changed. This prevents exactly that.

RailRotateMoveObj.Notes:
An object class that uses paths to move and rotate.

It also supports BCK, BTK, BTP, BRK and BVA animations. Animations must have the same name as the model in order to be played. The animations will start playing once the object loads. Also supports color change (ColorChange.brk) and texture change (TexChange.btk/.btp) animations as well as shadows (Shadow.bcsv).

Obj_arg0.Name: Color Frame
Obj_arg0.Description: If ColorChange.brk exists, this will define the color frame to be used.

Obj_arg1.Name: Texture Frame
Obj_arg1.Description: If TexChange.btp/.btk exists, this will define the texture frame to be used.

Obj_arg2.Name: Shadow Length
Obj_arg2.Description: If Shadow.bcsv exists, this defines the shadow's drop length.

Path_arg2.Name: Enable Orange Balls
Path_arg2.Description: If set, orange balls will be displayed along the path the object moves along.

Point_arg0.Name: Move Speed/Time
Point_arg0.Description: How this value acts is based on Point_arg7. -1 = The constant speed the object will use until the next point. 1 = The amount of time it takes to reach the next path point (in frames).

Point_arg1.Name: Acceleration Speed/Time
Point_arg1.Description: How this value acts is based on Point_arg7. -1 = The constant acceleration speed until the move speed is reached. 1 = Unknown behaviour

Point_arg2.Name: Rotate Speed/Time
Point_arg2.Description: How this value acts is based on Point_arg7. -1 = The constant speed the object will rotate at. 1 = The amount of time it takes to complete the rotation (in frames).

Point_arg3.Name: Rotation Angle
Point_arg3.Description: How much to rotate the object. Relative to the object's current rotation (eg. two path points are set to 180, the outcome is a full 360)

Point_arg4.Name: Rotation Axis
Point_arg4.Description: The axis of rotation to use

Point_arg5.Name: Wait Time
Point_arg5.Description: Stop at the current path point and wait the desired time (in frames).

Point_arg6.Name: Rotation Type
Point_arg6.Description: The type of rotation to use at this point.

Values.Notes: Finish rotation at the current point
Rotate between the current and next points

Point_arg7.Name: Speed Calculation Type
Point_arg7.Description: The type of calculations to perform on Point_arg0, 1, and 2.

SW_A.Description: Needs research

SW_B.Description: The object cannot move unless SW_B is activated.

Rail.Description: If not set, the game will crash when the platform tries to move.

RecoveryFloorControlArea.Notes: Normally, when the player falls into a PullBackArea, they won't be returned to the last position on Ice or GlassIce collision. Instead, the game treats several other collision types as safe rescuing positions. However, this area ignores the check for these two collision types so that these collision triangles are treated as proper rescuing positions.

RestartObj.Notes: A checkpoint flag used in several galaxies.

Obj_arg0.Name: Spawn Point ID
Obj_arg0.Description: The Start ID of the zone to respawn the player at.

Obj_arg0.Name: Speed
Obj_arg0.Description: The speed at which the radius increases.

Obj_arg1.Name: Delay
Obj_arg1.Description: Time until the rings disappear.

Obj_arg2.Name: Electricity Color
Obj_arg2.Description: Color of the rings.

RotateMoveObj.Notes:
An object that will rotate along it's axis.

It also supports BCK, BTK, BTP, BRK and BVA animations. Animations must have the same name as the model in order to be played. The animations will start playing once the object loads. Also supports color change (ColorChange.brk) and texture change (TexChange.btk/.btp) animations as well as shadows (Shadow.bcsv).

RotateMoveObjClipParts.Notes: Your typical RotateMoveObjParts, but with additional support for Clipping

Sandstorm.Notes: Moves on a path. Launches the player into the air once they get in its range. SunakazeKun objects may use two spiky rock obstacles to defend  themselves.

Obj_arg0.Name: Enable rock obstacles
Obj_arg0.Description: Enables the two spiky rock obstacles.

Obj_arg1.Name: Enable white color
Obj_arg1.Description: Starts the "White" color animation if enabled.

SW_A.Description: Activated whenever the player does not get launched.

Rail.Description: Specifies the movement path.

ScenarioStarter.Notes: The galaxy fly-in controller that sets up the fly-in path an sequence for a Star mission.

SimpleEnvironmentObj.Notes: Decorative objects that are meant to be placed in the background of a galaxy, such as asteroids.

DemoCast.Description: The object takes part in the cutscene.

SimpleMapObj.Notes: A generic map object with a model and optional collision. It also supports BCK, BTK, BTP, BRK and BVA animations. Animations must have the same name as the model in order to be played. The animations will start playing once the object loads. Also supports color change (ColorChange.brk) and texture change (TexChange.btk/.btp) animations as well as shadows (Shadow.bcsv).

Obj_arg0.Name: Color Frame
Obj_arg0.Description: If ColorChange.brk exists, this will define the color frame to be used.

Obj_arg1.Name: Texture Frame
Obj_arg1.Description: If TexChange.btp/.btk exists, this will define the texture frame to be used.

Obj_arg2.Name: Shadow Length
Obj_arg2.Description: If Shadow.bcsv exists, this defines the shadow's drop length.

DemoCast.Description: The object takes part in the cutscene.

SimpleMapObjFarMax.Notes: A variant of SimpleMapObj. This is a generic map object with a model, collision and a maximum far clipping distance. It also supports BCK, BTK, BTP, BRK and BVA animations. Animations must have the same name as the model in order to be played. The animations will start playing once the object loads. Also supports color change (ColorChange.brk) and texture change (TexChange.btk/.btp) animations as well as shadows (Shadow.bcsv).

Obj_arg0.Name: Color Frame
Obj_arg0.Description: If ColorChange.brk exists, this will define the color frame to be used.

Obj_arg1.Name: Texture Frame
Obj_arg1.Description: If TexChange.btp/.btk exists, this will define the texture frame to be used.

Obj_arg2.Name: Shadow Length
Obj_arg2.Description: If Shadow.bcsv exists, this defines the shadow's drop length.

DemoCast.Description: The object takes part in the cutscene.

SimpleMapObjWithEffect.Notes:
A variant of SimpleMapObj. This is a generic map object with a model, collision and looping particle effect. The UniqueName effect types that can be specified are EffectEmitStart and EffectEmitStart. If the object is called PeachCastleMeteor, it will ignore clipping checks.
It also supports BCK, BTK, BTP, BRK and BVA animations. Animations must have the same name as the model in order to be played. The animations will start playing once the object loads. Also supports color change (ColorChange.brk) and texture change (TexChange.btk/.btp) animations as well as shadows (Shadow.bcsv).

Obj_arg0.Name: Color Frame
Obj_arg0.Description: If ColorChange.brk exists, this will define the color frame to be used.

Obj_arg1.Name: Texture Frame
Obj_arg1.Description: If TexChange.btp/.btk exists, this will define the texture frame to be used.

Obj_arg2.Name: Shadow Length
Obj_arg2.Description: If Shadow.bcsv exists, this defines the shadow's drop length.

DemoCast.Description: The object takes part in the cutscene.

SimpleTextureSwitchChangeObj.Notes:
A variant of SimpleMapObj that starts the TexChange.btk animation and freezes its frame at 1 once its SW_A gets activated. Like SimpleMapObj, this is a generic map object with a model and collision.
It also supports BCK, BTK, BTP, BRK and BVA animations. Animations must have the same name as the model in order to be played. The animations will start playing once the object loads. Also supports color change (ColorChange.brk) and texture change (TexChange.btk/.btp) animations as well as shadows (Shadow.bcsv).

Obj_arg0.Name: Color Frame
Obj_arg0.Description: If ColorChange.brk exists, this will define the color frame to be used.

Obj_arg1.Name: Texture Frame
Obj_arg1.Description: If TexChange.btp/.btp exists, this will define the texture frame to be used.

Obj_arg2.Name: Shadow Length
Obj_arg2.Description: If Shadow.bcsv exists, this defines the shadow's drop length.

SW_A.Description: Applies frame 1 of the TexChange.btk animation.

DemoCast.Description: The object takes part in the cutscene.

SlopeRunningCancelArea.Notes: The player's running movement will be immediately stopped if they touch a steep surface inside this area.

Obj_arg3.Name: Color
Obj_arg3.Description: Color of the Star Bits.

Obj_arg0.Name: Number of Star Bits
Obj_arg0.Description: Amount of Star Bits to be distrbuted along the path or circle.

Obj_arg1.Name: Circle radius
Obj_arg1.Description: Radius of the Star Bit circle, only used if a path has not been assigned.

Obj_arg3.Name: Star Bit Color
Obj_arg3.Description: The color the Star Bits will be.

StrayTico.Notes: A Silver Star that is trapped in a bubble. The player usually has to collect five of them to make a Power Star appear.

SuperSpinDriver.Notes: A large star-shaped ring that launches the player from one point to another.

Obj_arg0.Name: Flight Time
Obj_arg0.Description: The amount of time the flight takes to complete (in frames). Default 300.

Obj_arg1.Name: Shadow Drop Distance
Obj_arg1.Description: The distance to drop the shadow. Default -1.

Obj_arg2.Name: Don't Grab Mario
Obj_arg2.Description: If set, the Launch Star won't pull the player towards it when they get near.

Obj_arg3.Name: Camera Count
Obj_arg3.Description: The number of Cameras to be read from the camera file.

Obj_arg4.Name: No Appear Jingle
Obj_arg4.Description: If enabled, the usual Launch Star appear jingle will not play.

Obj_arg5.Name: Landing Rotation
Obj_arg5.Description: The rotation that the player lands at. (NOTE: Needs further research as the rotation angle seems inconsistent)

Obj_arg7.Name: SpinDriverPathStorage Index
Obj_arg7.Description: The index of this launch star's path in the internal SpinDriverPathStorage class. This Arg is read by both games but only functions in SMG1.

SW_A.Description: If set, the Launch Star will be shrunken (and not usable) until the switch is activated.

Rail.Description: The path that the player will follow when flying.

SwitchArea.Notes: An area that activates a switch once the player enters it.

Obj_arg0.Name: Deactivate when area is left?
Obj_arg0.Description: If enabled, SW_A will be disabled after leaving the area.

Obj_arg1.Name: Invert Output
Obj_arg1.Description: If set, turns off SW_A instead of turning it on.

Obj_arg2.Name: Ground Use Only?
Obj_arg2.Description: If set, Mario must be on the ground inside the area to activate SW_A.

Obj_arg5.Name: Spin Drill Use Only?
Obj_arg5.Description: If set, requires the player be using a Spin Drill. (This arg is unused in the vanilla game)

SW_A.Description: The event to trigger when Mario enters the area.

Obj_arg0.Name: Holds Purple Coin
Obj_arg0.Description: If enabled, the Star Ball will hold a Purple Coin instead of a Power Star.

TicoSeedGuidanceCube.Notes: If the player stands inside this area, the game will display an explanation about how to feed a Hungry Luma with Star Bits. Does not work in SMG2.

TogepinAttackFoulArea.Notes: If the player enters this area, any TogepinScorer will detect this as a foul. If this happens, the player needs to get out of the area to make the minigame resume. This area has no effect if the player is rolling around using the Rock power-up.

ViewGroupCtrlArea.Notes: When entered by the player, all compatible objects in its ViewGroup will be forced to render.

Obj_arg0.Name: View Group ID
Obj_arg0.Description: The ViewGroup of objects that should be rendered.

Obj_arg1.Name: LOD Mode
Obj_arg1.Description: Overrides the LOD system by forcing the objects to use this specified LOD mode instead.

WoodBox.Notes: A wooden box that can be destroyed through most attacks. It can spawn various different items.

Obj_arg0.Name: Coin Count
Obj_arg0.Description: The number of coins to spawn when broken. Default 1.

Obj_arg1.Name: Hide Broken Pieces
Obj_arg1.Description: If enabled, the leftover broken pieces will be hidden.

Obj_arg2.Name: Starbit Count
Obj_arg2.Description: The number of coins to spawn when broken. Default 0.

Obj_arg3.Name: Play 'Secret Found' Sound
Obj_arg3.Description: If enabled, will play a jingle when broken.

Obj_arg4.Name: Spawn 1-UP
Obj_arg4.Description: If enabled, spawns a 1-UP mushroom when broken.

Obj_arg7.Name: Power Star ID
Obj_arg7.Description: The ID of the Power Star this crate will spawn. (The scenario needs to have it's PowerStarAppearObj set!)

YellowChip.Notes: A collectable yellow chip. Usually five of these are linked together by a YellowChipGroup to trigger a switch to spawn something like a Launch Star.

Obj_arg0.Name: Star Chip Group ID
Obj_arg0.Description: The ID of the YellowChipGroup this Star Chip is linked to.

Obj_arg3.Name: Inside Bubble
Obj_arg3.Description: If checked, the chip will spawn inside an air bubble.

Obj_arg4.Name: Shadow Drop Length
Obj_arg4.Description: The distance downwards that the object's shadow is projected.

Obj_arg5.Name: Shadow Shape
Obj_arg5.Description: The shape of the object's shadow.

YellowChipGroup.Notes:
A controller which activates SW_A when all Star Chip (YellowChip) objects linked to it by the obj_arg0 value are collected. It is recommended to have groups of 5 Star Chips.

This controller is also responsible for displaying the Star Chip Counter layout at the top of the screen.

Obj_arg0.Name: Group ID
Obj_arg0.Description: The ID of this group for Star Chips to link to.

Obj_arg2.Name: Star Chip Counter Display Range
Obj_arg2.Description: The distance the player has to be within of this object for the Star Chip Counter to be displayed.

Obj_arg3.Name: Re-activate When Previously Activated
Obj_arg3.Description: If checked, re-activates SW_A upon a soft reload (ex: after a death) if already activated before.

SW_A.Description: Activated when all linked Star Chips are collected.

YoshiBlock.Notes: A somewhat glitchy object that requires a custom file to be used. It loads the texture from YoshiBlock.arc/YoshiBlock/YoshiBlockTex.bti and it is a simple block that has no specific use. For some reason, it can't be seen in first-person view or during intro camera cutscenes.

Obj_arg0.Name: Unknown 0
Obj_arg0.Description: Possibly changes the animation from "Wait" to "WaitFree" (Needs research)

Obj_arg1.Name: No shadow
Obj_arg1.Description: If checked, the object doesn't cast a shadow.

YoshiCaptureGuidanceArea.Notes: If the player is riding Yoshi when inside this area, the game will display an explanation about how to use Yoshi Grapples.

YoshiEatGuidanceArea.Notes: If the player is riding Yoshi when inside this area, the game will display an explanation about how to eat items with Yoshi. If Obj_arg0 is set, it will explain how to shoot projectiles with Yoshi instead, provided that he is carrying a projectile in his mouth.

Obj_arg0.Name: Projectile Tutorial?
Obj_arg0.Description: If set, this will explain how to shoot projectiles with Yoshi instead.

SW_A.Description: Gets activated after displaying the tutorial once.

YoshiEgg.Notes: Handles spawning and respawning of Yoshi eggs.

Obj_arg0.Name: No Yoshi Egg
Obj_arg0.Description: If checked, no Yoshi Egg is spawned, only the nest.

YoshiFruit.Notes: An object which can be eatean by Yoshi and releases a Star Bit. If Yoshi eats ten of these, the player will be granted a 1-Up.

YoshiSendOffArea.Notes: If Yoshi is inside this area after the player dismounts him, he will play a special animation where he waves the player goodbye.

YukkinaGroundSnow.Notes: A destroyable snow spike object used by the Yukkina boss.

Obj_arg0.Name: Hits Needed For Coin
Obj_arg0.Description: The number of required hits on the object for it to spawn a coin.

Abekobe2DMoveLift.Name: Rightside Down -- Blank Moving Wood Platform
Abekobe2DMoveLift.Notes: A moving platform from Rightside Down Galaxy. It has a blank surface.

AbekobeCircleMoveLift.Name: Rightside Down -- Checkered Moving Wood Platform
AbekobeCircleMoveLift.Notes: A moving platform from Rightside Down Galaxy. It has a checker patterned surface.

AbekobeIntroducePlanet.Name: Rightside Down -- Intro Planet
AbekobeIntroducePlanet.Notes: The decorative building blocks planet that can be seen at the beginning of Rightside Down Galaxy.

AirBubble.Name: Air Bubble
AirBubble.Notes: A bubble that restores the player's air when collected underwater.

AirBubbleGenerator.Name: Air Bubble Generator
AirBubbleGenerator.Notes: A nozzle that periodically generates air bubbles.

AncientCage.Name: Clockwork Ruins -- Luma Cage
AncientCage.Notes: The red metal cage from Clockwork Ruins Galaxy.

AquariumPlanetA.Name: Cosmic Cove -- 2D Underwater Planet
AquariumPlanetA.Notes: The large planet found in the 2D underwater section from Cosmic Cove Galaxy.

AquariumPlanetB.Name: Cosmic Cove -- 2D Sea Mine Planet
AquariumPlanetB.Notes: The large planet found in Cosmic Cove Galaxy's 2D section that features Jammyfish and Sea Mines.

AquariumRailMoveObj.Name: Cosmic Cove -- Moving Gate
AquariumRailMoveObj.Notes: A moving metal gate from Cosmic Cove Galaxy.

AreaMoveSphere.Name: Collision Push Movement Area [Sphere]
AreaMoveSphere.Notes: Moves compatible objects if they are on AreaMove collision triangles.

ArrowBoard.Name: Arrow Sign
ArrowBoard.Notes: A large arrow-shaped sign with a red outline.

ArrowSwitch.Name: Arrow Switch
ArrowSwitch.Notes: An arrow-shaped switch that rotates once it gets triggered.

ArrowSwitchMulti.Name: Multi-Use Arrow Switch
ArrowSwitchMulti.Notes: An arrow-shaped switch that rotates once it gets triggered. Can be triggered multiple times.

ArrowSwitchTarget.Name: Multi-Use Arrow Switch Target
ArrowSwitchTarget.Notes: A target that triggers a switch based off of the state of the ArrowSwitchMulti that it belongs to.

AssemblyBlock.Name: Generic Space Junk Block [Unused]
AssemblyBlock.Notes: A Space Junk block that retrieves a proper model using ShapeModelNo. However, no more models exist for this object.

AssemblyBlockPartsIceB.Name: Small Icy Space Junk Block
AssemblyBlockPartsIceB.Notes: A small square-shaped icy version of a Space Junk Block.

AssemblyBlockPartsIceC.Name: Very Talll Icy Space Junk Block
AssemblyBlockPartsIceC.Notes: A very tall square-shaped icy version of a Space Junk Block.

AssemblyBlockPartsIceD.Name: Tall Icy Space Junk Block
AssemblyBlockPartsIceD.Notes: A tall square-shaped icy version of a Space Junk Block.

AssemblyBlockPartsIceE.Name: Narrow Icy Space Junk Block
AssemblyBlockPartsIceE.Notes: A narrow square-shaped icy version of a Space Junk Block.

AssemblyBlockPartsTimerA.Name: Timed Space Junk Block
AssemblyBlockPartsTimerA.Notes: A long rectangular transparent Space Junk Block; used in Bowser's Galaxy Reactor.

AssemblyBlockPlanet.Name: Space Junk -- Silver Star Planet
AssemblyBlockPlanet.Notes: The planet at the start of the Silver Star section in the first mission of Space Junk Galaxy.

AsteroidA.Name: Large Decorative Asteroids
AsteroidA.Notes: A group of many large asteroids that serve as decoration.

AsteroidB.Name: Small Decorative Asteroids
AsteroidB.Notes: A group of many small asteroids that serve as decoration.

AsteroidBlockPlanet.Name: 8-Bit Mario/Luigi Planet Parts
AsteroidBlockPlanet.Notes: The lava, swamp platforms and large brick platform that serve as the basis of the 8-Bit Mario/Luigi planet from Toy Time Galaxy and Mario Squared Galaxy.

AsteroidBlockRotateStepA.Name: Toy Time -- Yellow Rotating Platform
AsteroidBlockRotateStepA.Notes: A yellow rotating platform used on the 8-Bit Mario planet in Toy Time Galaxy.

AsteroidC.Name: Medium Decorative Asteroids
AsteroidC.Notes: A group of many medium-sized asteroids that serve as decoration.

AsteroidD.Name: Lush Decorative Asteroids
AsteroidD.Notes: A group of many lush asteroids that serve as decoration.

AsteroidMoveA.Name: Moving Asteroid Cluster
AsteroidMoveA.Notes: A group of many small asteroids that can move on a path.

AstroBaseA.Name: Comet Observatory -- Grassy Region
AstroBaseA.Notes: The section of the Comet Observatory where the Terrace and the Fountain are located.

AstroBaseB.Name: Comet Observatory -- Library Region
AstroBaseB.Notes: The section of the Comet Observatory where the Kitchen and the Bedroom are located.

AstroBaseC.Name: Comet Observatory -- Upper Region
AstroBaseC.Notes: The section of the Comet Observatory where the Engine Room and the Garden are located.

AstroBaseCenterA.Name: Comet Observatory -- Big Slope
AstroBaseCenterA.Notes: The big slope found below the Engine Room in the Comet Observatory.

AstroBaseCenterB.Name: Comet Observatory -- Beacon Holder
AstroBaseCenterB.Notes: The two cones that hold the Beacon in place in the Comet Observatory.

AstroBaseCenterTop.Name: Comet Observatory -- Peak
AstroBaseCenterTop.Notes: The top of the Comet Observatory where a 1-Up can be found.

AstroBaseKitchen.Name: Comet Observatory -- Kitchen Steps
AstroBaseKitchen.Notes: The steps that lead up to the Kitchen in the Comet Observatory.

AstroChangeStageCube.Name: Comet Observatory Change Stage Area [Cube]
AstroChangeStageCube.Notes: An area that will exit the current scene and start another one. For example, this is used to go to the different Domes on the Comet Observatory. The cube's origin is the base's center.

AstroChildRoom.Name: Comet Observatory -- Gateway Planet
AstroChildRoom.Notes: The small planet from the Comet Observatory that leads to Gateway Galaxy.

AstroCore.Name: Comet Observatory Beacon
AstroCore.Notes: The glowing Beacon that serves as the engine of the Comet Observatory.

AstroCountDownPlate.Name: Comet Observatory Star Countdown
AstroCountDownPlate.Notes: The number located at the start of the Comet Observatory that counts down the amount of stars you need to finish the game.

AstroDecoratePartsA.Name: Comet Observatory -- Beacon Ring
AstroDecoratePartsA.Notes: The red-purple ring found around the Beacon in the Comet Observatory.

AstroDecoratePartsGearA.Name: Comet Observatory -- Decorative Gears
AstroDecoratePartsGearA.Notes: The rotating gears found inside the glass of the Comet Observatory.

AstroDomeAsteroid.Name: Level Select Asteroids
AstroDomeAsteroid.Notes: A group of many rotating asteroids that are found in the galaxy select of the Domes.

AstroDomeBlueStar.Name: Level Select Pull Star
AstroDomeBlueStar.Notes: A variation of the Pull Star that takes you to the galaxy select within Domes.

AstroDomeComet.Name: Level Select Comet
AstroDomeComet.Notes: The decoration used when a galaxy in the galaxy select has a Comet.

AstroDomeDemoAstroGalaxy.Name: Level Select Miniature Comet Observatory
AstroDomeDemoAstroGalaxy.Notes: A small version of the Comet Observatory that can be seen when the player flies to a galaxy in a Dome.

AstroDomeDemoStarter.Name: Level Select Fly-Out Cutscene
AstroDomeDemoStarter.Notes: Sets up the cutscene for when the player flies to a galaxy in a Dome.

AstroDomeEntrance.Name: Comet Observatory -- Dome
AstroDomeEntrance.Notes: The entrances to the several Domes in the Comet Observatory.

AstroDomeGalaxySelector.Name: Level Select Controller
AstroDomeGalaxySelector.Notes: A controller for the galaxy select in the Domes.

AstroDomeSky.Name: Dome Sky
AstroDomeSky.Notes: The starry ocean sky models used in the Domes.

AstroDomeSkyA.Name: Bigmouth Sky
AstroDomeSkyA.Notes: The starry ocean sky model from Bigmouth Galaxy.

AstroLibrary.Name: Comet Observatory -- Library Exterior
AstroLibrary.Notes: The exterior of the Comet Observatory's library.

AstroMapBoard.Name: Comet Observatory Map Screen
AstroMapBoard.Notes: A huge screen that displays the map of the Comet Observatory.

AstroOverlookAreaCylinder.Name: Show Comet Observatory Labels Area [Cylinder]
AstroOverlookAreaCylinder.Notes: Displays the labels for the different parts of the Comet Observatory. Requires an actual AstroOverlookObj placed in the stage.

AstroOverlookObj.Name: Show Comet Observatory Labels Controller
AstroOverlookObj.Notes: A controller that will show the name labels for the different parts of the Comet Observatory if the player stands inside an AstroOverlookAreaCylinder.

AstroParking.Name: Comet Observatory -- Garage
AstroParking.Notes: The garage section in which the Toad Brigade's Starshroom is parked.

AstroRoomLibrary.Name: Comet Observatory -- Library Interior
AstroRoomLibrary.Notes: The interior of the Comet Observatory's Library.

AstroRotateStepA.Name: Comet Observatory -- Green Rotating Platforms
AstroRotateStepA.Notes: A set of green rotating platforms found on the lower level of the Comet Observatory.

AstroRotateStepB.Name: Comet Observatory -- Yellow Rotating Platforms
AstroRotateStepB.Notes: A set of yellow rotating platforms found on the upper level of the Comet Observatory.

AstroStarPlate.Name: Comet Observatory -- Dome Pipes
AstroStarPlate.Notes: The decorative pipes in the Comet Observatory that power the Domes.

AstroTorchLightBlue.Name: Blue Comet Observatory Torch Light
AstroTorchLightBlue.Notes: A blue torch light that was meant to be used in the Comet Observatory.

AstroTorchLightRed.Name: Red Comet Observatory Torch Light
AstroTorchLightRed.Notes: The red torch light used in the Comet Observatory.

AttackRock.Name: Bowser Attack Rock [Fight]
AttackRock.Notes: A yellow orb that appears during the boss fights against Bowser.

AttackRockFinal.Name: Bowser Attack Rock [Final Fight]
AttackRockFinal.Notes: A yellow orb that appears during the final boss fight against Bowser.

AttackRockTutorial.Name: Bowser Attack Rock [Stage]
AttackRockTutorial.Notes: A yellow orb that appears before the fights against Bowser.

AudioEffectArea.Name: Audio Effect Area
AudioEffectArea.Notes: Enables a different audio effect once entered.

AudioEffectCube.Name: Audio Effect Area [Cube]
AudioEffectCube.Notes: Enables a different audio effect once entered. The cube's origin is the base's center.

AudioEffectCylinder.Name: Audio Effect Area [Cylinder]
AudioEffectCylinder.Notes: Enables a different audio effect once entered.

AudioEffectSphere.Name: Audio Effect Area [Sphere]
AudioEffectSphere.Notes: Enables a different audio effect once entered.

AuroraSky.Name: Freezeflame Sky
AuroraSky.Notes: The sky model from Freezeflame Galaxy that features auroras.

BackgroundComet.Name: Starship Mario -- Rosalina's Comet
BackgroundComet.Notes: The large egg-shaped Comet that appears during Starship Mario's ending cutscene.

BakuBaku.Name: Mattermouth
BakuBaku.Notes: A gluttonous skull enemy from Haunty Halls Galaxy.

BakubakuCircleConveyor.Name: Haunty Halls -- Small Rotating Carpet Platform

BakuBakuClipStep.Name: Lava Lair -- Mattermouth Carpet
BakuBakuClipStep.Notes: The large carpet from Bowser's Lava Lair that is eaten away by Mattermouths.

BallBeamer.Name: Ball Beamer
BallBeamer.Notes: A yellow enemy with a metal nut on its head that periodically emits spherical rings of electricity.

Balloonfish.Name: Porcupuffer
Balloonfish.Notes: A purple blowfish enemy from Drip Drop Galaxy and Cosmic Cove Galaxy.

BalloonFruit.Name: Blimp Fruit
BalloonFruit.Notes: The blue fruit that Yoshi can eat to expand and fly like a balloon.

BallOpener.Name: Generic Star Ball Opener
BallOpener.Notes: A metal hole with a blue edge that is used to crack Star Balls in Rolling Green Galaxy and Rolling Gizmo Galaxy.

BallOpenerSlider.Name: Rolling Coaster -- Star Ball Opener
BallOpenerSlider.Notes: The round planet from Rolling Coaster Galaxy that features a hole to crack open the Star Ball.

BallOpenerTamakoro.Name: Rolling Masterpiece -- Star Ball Opener
BallOpenerTamakoro.Notes: A pink pencil platform from Rolling Masterpiece Galaxy that features a hole to crack open the Star Ball.

BallRail.Name: Star Ball Rail
BallRail.Notes: An invisible path that the Star Ball will move on once touched.

Banekiti.Name: Banekiti
Banekiti.Notes: A mechanical spring enemy that bounces off Boo Mario upon contact. It is used in Boo's Boneyard Galaxy.

BarrelCloudActionPlanet.Name: Galaxy Generator -- Cloud Flower Planet
BarrelCloudActionPlanet.Notes: The planet from Bowser's Galaxy Generator's section that features Cloud Flowers and Bullet Bills.

BarrelCloudActionRotateLiftA.Name: Galaxy Generator -- Rotating Stone Lift
BarrelCloudActionRotateLiftA.Notes: A rotating cylinder from Bowser's Galaxy Generator that has some small platforms attached to it. Used in the section that features Cloud Flowers and Bullet Bills.

BarrelColonyDoor.Name: Sky Station -- Cylindrical Banzai Bill Planet Door
BarrelColonyDoor.Notes: The small door that covers the entrance into the cylindrical planet from Sky Station Galaxy's second Star.

BarrelColonyInnerPlanet.Name: Sky Station -- Cylindrical Banzai Bill Planet Interior
BarrelColonyInnerPlanet.Notes: The interior parts of the large cylindrical planet from Sky Station Galaxy's second Star.

BarrelColonyLift.Name: Sky Station -- Rotating Metal Lift
BarrelColonyLift.Notes: A rotating cylinder that has four smaller platforms attached to it. It can be found inside the large cylindrical planet from Sky Station Galaxy's second Star.

BarrelColonyOuterPlanet.Name: Sky Station -- Cylindrical Banzai Bill Planet Exterior
BarrelColonyOuterPlanet.Notes: The exterior parts of the large cylindrical planet from Sky Station Galaxy's second Star.

BarrelElectricRailColonyPlanet.Name: Space Storm -- Long Cylindrical Satellite Planet

PlaneCircularModeCube.Name: Circular 2D Movement Area [Cube]
PlaneCircularModeCube.Notes: An area that restricts movement to a 2D plane when entered. The movement direction is adjusted for moving around a circular center point. The cube's origin is the base's center.

PlaneCollisionArea.Name: Extended Item Sensor Area
PlaneCollisionArea.Notes: An area which extends the sensor range when trying to collect items along the camera's view direction. For example, this allows the player to collect an item while they stand behind or in front of it.

PlaneCollisionCube.Name: Extended Item Sensor Area [Cube]
PlaneCollisionCube.Notes: An area which extends the sensor range when trying to collect items along the camera's view direction. For example, this allows the player to collect an item while thy stand behind or in front of it. The cube's origin is the base's center.

PlaneModeArea.Name: 2D Movement Area
PlaneModeArea.Notes: An area that restricts movement to a 2D plane when entered.

PlaneModeCube.Name: 2D Movement Area [Cube]
PlaneModeCube.Notes: An area that restricts movement to a 2D plane when entered. The cube's origin is the base's center.

PlanetDisk.Name: "PlanetDisk" [Unused]
PlanetDisk.Notes: An unused and unfinished disk-shaped planet with a large flower field, two realistic trees and a big mushroom.

PlanetRocket.Name: Space Junk -- Rocket Planet
PlanetRocket.Notes: The large rocket planet that appears in Space Junk Galaxy and Ghostly Galaxy.

Plant.Name: Vine Sproutle
Plant.Notes: A vine that you spin to grab hold of, and shake the Wii Remote to move on it.

PlantA.Name: Decorative Plant A
PlantA.Notes:
A more advanced flower spawner which uses ShapeModelNo for all the different plants. The following shape IDs and colors are available:
0 Violets
- 0 Yellow
- 1 Purple
- 2 Red
- 3 White
1 Short Bush
2 Mushrooms
3 Clover
4 Dead Bush
5 Red Flower
- 0 Red
- 1 White
6 Bubbly Flower
7 Yellow Flower
- 0 Blue
- 1 Yellow
8 Tall Bush

PlantB.Name: Decorative Plant B
PlantB.Notes:
A more advanced flower spawner which uses ShapeModelNo for all the different plants. The following shape IDs and colors are available:
0 Tulips
- 0 Pink
- 1 Yellow
- 2 Purple
3 Lily of the Valley

PlantC.Name: Decorative Plant C
PlantC.Notes:
A more advanced flower spawner which uses ShapeModelNo for all the different plants. The following shape IDs and colors are available:
0 Cosmos
1 Round Bush
- 0 Pink
- 1 Red
- 2 White

PlantD.Name: Decorative Plant D
PlantD.Notes:
A more advanced flower spawner which uses ShapeModelNo for all the different plants. The following shape IDs and colors are available:
1 Lily
- 0 Red
- 1 Pink
- 2 Yellow
- 3 White
2 Sunflower

PlantSlider.Name: One-Way Vine Sproutle
PlantSlider.Notes: A vine that can be used to reach other places in a galaxy. This one leads into one direction only and the player doesn't have to shake the Wiimote.

PlayAttackMan.Name: The Chimp
PlayAttackMan.Notes: A blue monkey NPC who appears in some galaxies inviting the player to a minigame challenge.

PlayerMorphLimitArea.Name: Restrict Power-Up Usage Area
PlayerMorphLimitArea.Notes: Restricts the use of power-ups inside this area. If the player leaves the area, the effects of the collected power-up wear off.

PlayerSeCube.Name: Player Falling Sound Area [Cube]
PlayerSeCube.Notes: Plays the "long fall" sound effect while the player is airborne inside this area. The cube's origin is the base's center.

PlayerSeCylinder.Name: Player Falling Sound Area [Cylinder]
PlayerSeCylinder.Notes: Plays the "long fall" sound effect while the player is airborne inside this area.

PlayerSeSphere.Name: Player Falling Sound Area [Sphere]
PlayerSeSphere.Notes: Plays the "long fall" sound effect while the player is airborne inside this area.

PlayerSideRetainOffArea.Name: Disable Movement Direction Retention Area
PlayerSideRetainOffArea.Notes: This area adjusts the player's movement direction to the current camera angle instead of keeping the direction the joystick was held in before moving.

Poihana.Name: Cataquack
Poihana.Notes: A blue duck-like enemy that can toss the player high into the air.

PoihanaMazePlanet.Name: Gold Leaf -- Cataquack Maze Planet
PoihanaMazePlanet.Notes: The grassy maze-like planet visited in the second mission.

PoihanaRelayPlanet.Name: Gold Leaf -- Spherical Cataquack Planet
PoihanaRelayPlanet.Notes: A small spherical wooden planet with a pond.

PoisonSwanpRailMoveSeesaw.Name: Boom Bunker -- Tilting Seesaw Platform
PoisonSwanpRailMoveSeesaw.Notes: A tilting seesaw-like platform used on the Dark Matter planet in Bowser Jr.'s Boom Bunker.

PoisonSwanpSeesawMovePlanet.Name: Boom Bunker -- Dark Matter Planet
PoisonSwanpSeesawMovePlanet.Notes: The planet filled with Dark Matter used in the Comet mission of Bowser Jr.'s Boom Bunker.

Pole.Name: Climbable Pole
Pole.Notes: A standard climbable pole that can be climbed from all directions.

Pole2Way.Name: Wood Pole [Two-Sided Climbing]
Pole2Way.Notes: An alternate version of the wooden pole which can be climbed on two sides only.

PoleNoModel.Name: Invisible Climbable Pole
PoleNoModel.Notes: An invisible version of a pole.

PoleObstaclePartsA.Name: Rolling Masterpiece -- Green Paintbrush
PoleObstaclePartsA.Notes: A large green paintbrush used in Rolling Masterpiece Galaxy.

PoleObstaclePartsB.Name: Rolling Masterpiece -- Red Paintbrush
PoleObstaclePartsB.Notes: A large red paintbrush used in Rolling Masterpiece Galaxy.

PoleObstaclePartsC.Name: Rolling Masterpiece -- Blue Paintbrush
PoleObstaclePartsC.Notes: A large blue paintbrush used in Rolling Masterpiece Galaxy.

PoleObstaclePartsD.Name: Rolling Masterpiece -- Yellow Paintbrush
PoleObstaclePartsD.Notes: A large yellow paintbrush used in Rolling Masterpiece Galaxy.

PoleSquare.Name: Wood Pole
PoleSquare.Notes: A wooden square pole that can be climbed on four sides.

PoleSquareNoModel.Name: Invisible Wood Pole
PoleSquareNoModel.Notes: An invisible version of the square-shaped pole.

PoleTreeA.Name: Bubbly Tree
PoleTreeA.Notes: A round tree used in Throwback Galaxy that can be climbed.

PoleTreeB.Name: Pine Tree
PoleTreeB.Notes: A pine tree used in Fluffy Bluff Galaxy that can be climbed.

PoleUnizoPlanet.Name: "PoleUnizoPlanet" [Unused]
PoleUnizoPlanet.Notes: An unused rocky planet that was intended to be used in Deep Dark Galaxy. The name refers to the Urchin enemies.

Polta.Name: Bouldergeist
Polta.Notes: The boss fought at the end of the third mission in Ghostly Galaxy and Boss Blitz Galaxy.

PoltaBattlePlanet.Name: Ghostly -- Bouldergeist Planet
PoltaBattlePlanet.Notes: The planet where Bouldergeist is fought in Ghostly Galaxy.

PoltaBattlePlanetPartsA.Name: Ghostly -- Bouldergeist Planet Platforms
PoltaBattlePlanetPartsA.Notes: The stone platforms that lead to Bouldergeist's planet in Ghostly Galaxy.

Pompon2Plant.Name: Bubbly Plant
Pompon2Plant.Notes: A bubbly plant that releases some items when touched; used in Honeyhive Galaxy and Gold Leaf Galaxy.

Pompon4Plant.Name: Bubbly Plant without Effects
Pompon4Plant.Notes: A bubbly plant that releases some items when touched; used in Honeyhive Galaxy. It does not emit any particle effects when touched.

Popo.Name: Smeech
Popo.Notes: A pink enemy that tries to suck on Yoshi, but runs away from the player under normal circumstances.

PositiveDice.Name: Positive Chance Cube
PositiveDice.Notes: A dice block that can reward either a Star Bit or a 1-Up Mushroom.

PostFogArea.Name: Post Fog Area
PostFogArea.Notes: An area that renders a fog post effect on the screen when entered.

PostOutlineArea.Name: Post Outline Area
PostOutlineArea.Notes: An area that renders a thick outline on the screen when entered.

PowerStar.Name: Power Star
PowerStar.Notes: A shiny Power Star that acts as the main collectible in most galaxies.

PowerStarAppearPoint.Name: Power Star Spawn Point
PowerStarAppearPoint.Notes: A spawn point where a grouped Power Star can appear.

PowerStarHalo.Name: Power Star Light
PowerStarHalo.Notes: The large light given off by a Power Star. The model differs between the two games.

PowerStarKeeperA.Name: Battlerock -- Red Rotating Metal Shields
PowerStarKeeperA.Notes: A pair of red rotating metal shields that are used as an obstacle during the second mission.

PowerStarKeeperB.Name: Battlerock -- Yellow Rotating Metal Shields
PowerStarKeeperB.Notes: A pair of yellow rotating metal shields that are used as an obstacle during the second mission.

PowerStarKeeperC.Name: Battlerock -- Blue Rotating Metal Shields
PowerStarKeeperC.Notes: A set of four blue rotating metal shields that are used as an obstacle during the second mission.

PrepareKoopaFinalDemoObj.Name: Before Final Bowser Cutscene Object Holder
PrepareKoopaFinalDemoObj.Notes: A holder that creates and registers the objects used during the cutscene before entering Bowser's Galaxy Generator.

PrologueDirector.Name: Star Festival Prologue Controller
PrologueDirector.Notes: A cutscene controller that manages major parts of the prologue sequence. This includes the picture book story, Peach's letter and the short scene where Mario enters the castle town.

ProminenceSetA.Name: Fiery Flotilla -- Decorative Fire Balls
ProminenceSetA.Notes: A set of fire balls used in the background of Bowser Jr.'s Fiery Flotilla.

PTimerSwitch.Name: P-Switch
PTimerSwitch.Notes: A blue P-Switch that disappears and activates a switch when stepped on.

PuffballPlanetA.Name: Gusty Garden -- Flower Hill Planet
PuffballPlanetA.Notes: The starting planet with the many flowers.

PuffballPlanetB.Name: Gusty Garden -- Stone Blocks Planet
PuffballPlanetB.Notes: A grassy planet with some ruined stone structures and flowers.

PuffballPlanetC.Name: Gusty Garden -- C-Shaped Stone Blocks Planet
PuffballPlanetC.Notes: A C-shaped grass planet featuring some stone blocks and flowers.

Pukupuku.Name: Cheep Cheep
Pukupuku.Notes: A fish enemy used in underwater levels.

PukupukuGambolPlanet.Name: Deep Dark -- Cheep Cheep Planet
PukupukuGambolPlanet.Notes: A small spherical planet with water that is visited during the second mission.

PukupukuWaterSurface.Name: Water Surface Cheep Cheep
PukupukuWaterSurface.Notes: A fish enemy that is intended to swim on the water's surface.

PullBackArea.Name: Rescue from Falling Area
PullBackArea.Notes: An area that, when entered, returns the player to the last safe position they stood on before falling off.

PullBackCube.Name: Rescue from Falling Area [Cube]
PullBackCube.Notes: An area that, when entered, returns the player to the last safe position they stood on before falling off. The cube's origin is the base's center.

PullBackCylinder.Name: Rescue from Falling Area [Cylinder]
PullBackCylinder.Notes: An area that, when entered, returns the player to the last safe position they stood on before falling off.

PullTargetBridge.Name: "PullTargetBridge" [Broken]
PullTargetBridge.Notes: Model files have been removed. Therefore, the object is useless.

PullTargetDrawer.Name: Wooden Yoshi Pull Block
PullTargetDrawer.Notes: A large wooden block that can be pulled out of a wall using Yoshi's tongue.

PunchBox.Name: Brick Block
PunchBox.Notes: A standard Brick Block that can be destroyed.

PunchBox2D.Name: Brick Block [2D]
PunchBox2D.Notes: A small Brick Block variant that is used in the prologue.

PunchingKinoko.Name: Stretch Plant
PunchingKinoko.Notes: A green plant that the player can fling around to damage other objects.

PurpleCoin.Name: Purple Coin
PurpleCoin.Notes: A Purple Coin from Purple Comet missions that spawns a Power Star once 100 of them are collected.

PurpleCoinCompleteWatcher.Name: All Purple Coins Collected Switch
PurpleCoinCompleteWatcher.Notes: A controller that activates a switch when 100 Purple Coins have been collected.

PurpleCoinStarter.Name: Purple Coin Appearance Controller
PurpleCoinStarter.Notes: A controller that will hide all Purple Coins and the UI until it gets activated.

PurpleRailCoin.Name: Purple Coin Line
PurpleRailCoin.Notes: An object that creates a line of Purple Coins.

PusherWall.Name: Clockwork Ruins -- Pusher Wall [Remaining]
PusherWall.Notes: A purple wall that pushes objects; used on the gravity planet in Clockwork Ruins Galaxy.

PusherWallDisappear.Name: Clockwork Ruins -- Pusher Wall [Disappearing]
PusherWallDisappear.Notes: A purple wall that pushes objects and is destroyed after using the gravity-arrow switch on the gravity planet in Clockwork Ruins Galaxy.

PusherWallPlanet.Name: Clockwork Ruins -- Gravity Planet
PusherWallPlanet.Notes: The second planet used in the first mission of Clockwork Ruins Galaxy.

PusherWallPlanetParts.Name: Clockwork Ruins -- Disappearing Gravity Planet Wall
PusherWallPlanetParts.Notes: The back wall of the gravity planet used in Clockwork Ruins Galaxy.

Pyudon.Name: Flaptack
Pyudon.Notes: A blue bird-like enemy that smacks onto the player if they walk under it.

QuakeEffectAreaCube.Name: Earthquake Area [Cube]
QuakeEffectAreaCube.Notes: An area that periodically shakes the camera and plays a quaking sound effect while the player is inside it.

QuarterRollGravityRoomArrow.Name: Dreadnought -- 2D Interior Gravity Indicator
QuarterRollGravityRoomArrow.Notes: A pair of arrows that are used to indicate the gravity direction in the 2D interior section.

QuarterRollGravityRoomPlanet.Name: Dreadnought -- 2D Interior Section
QuarterRollGravityRoomPlanet.Notes: The large 2D interior section that features several large pistons.

QuestionBoxMoveStepA.Name: Gusty Garden -- Large Gravity Scramble Block
QuestionBoxMoveStepA.Notes: A large rotating block used in the third mission.

QuestionBoxMoveStepB.Name: Gusty Garden -- Small Rotated Gravity Scramble Block
QuestionBoxMoveStepB.Notes: A small moving block used in the third mission.

QuestionBoxMoveStepC.Name: Gusty Garden -- Small Gravity Scramble Block
QuestionBoxMoveStepC.Notes: A small moving block used in the third mission.

QuestionBoxPlanetA.Name: Gusty Garden -- Gravity Scramble Starting Planet
QuestionBoxPlanetA.Notes: The first group of large block planets visited during the third mission.

QuestionBoxPlanetB.Name: Gusty Garden -- Gravity Scramble Block Pair Planet
QuestionBoxPlanetB.Notes: A pair of two large block planets visited during the third mission.

QuestionBoxPlanetC.Name: Gusty Garden -- Gravity Scramble Long Planet
QuestionBoxPlanetC.Notes: The long group of large block planets visited during the third mission.

QuestionBoxPlanetD.Name: Gusty Garden -- Gravity Scramble Cylinder Planet
QuestionBoxPlanetD.Notes: A small cylindrical planet segment visited during the third mission.

QuestionBoxPlanetE.Name: Gusty Garden -- Gravity Scramble Cannons Planet
QuestionBoxPlanetE.Notes: The last group of large block planets visited during the third mission.

QuestionCoin.Name: ? Coin
QuestionCoin.Notes: A large yellow Coin with a question mark symbol on it that activates something when collected.

QuestionFlowerGardenPlanet.Name: Gusty Garden -- Question Planet
QuestionFlowerGardenPlanet.Notes: The planet shaped like a question mark used in Gusty Garden Galaxy.

QuickSand2DMovePartsA.Name: Dusty Dune -- 2D Underground Rotating Gear
QuickSand2DMovePartsA.Notes: A rotating gear used in the underground section of the first mission.

Quicksand2DPlanet.Name: Dusty Dune -- 2D Underground Section
Quicksand2DPlanet.Notes: The large 2D underground section visited during the first mission.

Rabbit.Name: Star Bunny
Rabbit.Notes: A rabbit that be found in several galaxies, including Gold Leaf Galaxy and Freezy Flake Galaxy.

RaceRail.Name: Race Path
RaceRail.Notes: An object that is used to set up the route for several racing minigames such as Ray Surfing and Glide Races.

RailCoin.Name: Coin Line
RailCoin.Notes: An object that creates a path of Coins.

RailMoveDisappearStep.Name: Throwback -- Collapsing Stone Platform
RailMoveDisappearStep.Notes: A stone platform that falls when the player steps on it.

RailMoveMiniPlanetObjA.Name: Yoshi Star -- Moving Dirt Planet
RailMoveMiniPlanetObjA.Notes: A small moving dirt planet from Yoshi Star Galaxy.

RailMoveMiniPlanetObjB.Name: Yoshi Star -- Moving Stone Planet
RailMoveMiniPlanetObjB.Notes: A small moving stone planet from Yoshi Star Galaxy.

RailMoveNormalLift.Name: Flash Black -- Yellow Moving Platform
RailMoveNormalLift.Notes: A simple moving platform that is yellow.

RailMoveWaterAreaPlanet.Name: Cosmic Cove -- Water Cubes Planet
RailMoveWaterAreaPlanet.Notes: The planet with moving water cubes used in the second mission of Cosmic Cove Galaxy.

RailMoveWaterObj.Name: Cosmic Cove -- Moving Water Cube
RailMoveWaterObj.Notes: A cube-shaped body of water from Cosmic Cove Galaxy.

RailObj.Name: Subpath
RailObj.Notes: This object is required by ElectricRailTwoPoint and LavaSeparateWaterfall. It sets multiple paths for an object to use.

RailPlacementPoleObstacle.Name: Rolling Masterpiece -- Paintbrush Line
RailPlacementPoleObstacle.Notes: An object used to create a line of paintbrushes; used in Rolling Masterpiece Galaxy.

RainCloud.Name: Rain Cloud
RainCloud.Notes: A cloud that is usually raining. The player can stand on it using the Bee power-up.

RasterScrollArea.Name: Wobbling Screen Area
RasterScrollArea.Notes: An area that, when entered, creates a wobbling screen effect.

RasterScrollCube.Name: Wobbling Screen Area [Cube]
RasterScrollCube.Notes: An area that, when entered, creates a wobbling screen effect. The cube's origin is the base's center.

RayGunPlanet.Name: Toy Time -- Large Screw Planet
RayGunPlanet.Notes: The planet with the large screw visited during the second mission.

RayGunPlanetPartsGear.Name: Toy Time -- Large Screw Planet Gear
RayGunPlanetPartsGear.Notes: A rotating wood gear used on the large screw planet.

RayGunPlanetPartsScrew.Name: Toy Time -- Large Screw
RayGunPlanetPartsScrew.Notes: The large screw used during the second mission.

RecoveryFloorControlArea.Name: Enable Ice Collision Rescue Position Area
RecoveryFloorControlArea.Notes: An area that enables saving the last position on Ice or GlassIce collision as a safe rescuing position.

RedBlueExStepA.Name: Flip-Swap -- Starting Platforms
RedBlueExStepA.Notes: A set of platforms used as the starting planet of Flip-Swap Galaxy.

RedBlueExStepB.Name: Flip-Swap -- Goomba Platform
RedBlueExStepB.Notes: A rectangular platform where Goombas are located in Flip-Swap Galaxy.

RedBlueExStepC.Name: Flip-Swap -- Checkpoint Platform
RedBlueExStepC.Notes: The staircase platform where the checkpoint is located in Flip-Swap Galaxy.

RedBlueExStepD.Name: Flip-Swap -- Cosmic Guide Platform
RedBlueExStepD.Notes: The platform where the Cosmic Guide appears in Flip-Swap Galaxy.

RedBlueExStepE.Name: Flip-Swap -- Small Platform
RedBlueExStepE.Notes: A pair of two blocks that serve as a platform; used in Flip-Swap Galaxy.

RedBlueExStepF.Name: Flip-Swap -- Power Star Platform
RedBlueExStepF.Notes: The platform where the Power Star is located in Flip-Swap Galaxy.

RedBlueTurnBlock.Name: Flip-Swap Platform
RedBlueTurnBlock.Notes: A red and blue flipping platform used mainly in Flip-Swap Galaxy.

RelayDrill2DPlanet.Name: Spin-Dig -- Cylinder Planet
RelayDrill2DPlanet.Notes: The cylindrical-shaped planet used in the second mission of Spin-Dig Galaxy.

RelayPlanetA.Name: Small Asteroid Planet A
RelayPlanetA.Notes: A small asteroid used in the background of certain galaxies, such as Space Junk Galaxy and Spin Dig Galaxy.

RelayPlanetB.Name: Small Asteroid Planet B
RelayPlanetB.Notes: The asteroid planet with the Launch Star leading to the Fiery Dino Piranha planet in Boss Blitz Galaxy.

RelayPlanetC.Name: E3 Demo -- Wood Planet
RelayPlanetC.Notes: An unused wooden planet that was used in the E3 2006 demo.

RelayPlanetD.Name: Bubble Blast -- Blue Asteroid Planet
RelayPlanetD.Notes: A small blue asteroid seen in the galaxy's background scenery.

RelayPlanetE.Name: Deep Dark -- Wood Planet
RelayPlanetE.Notes: A small wooden planet where the player encounters many Octoguys.

RelayPlanetF.Name: Toy Time -- Rusty Metal Planet
RelayPlanetF.Notes: A small rusty metal planet seen in the galaxy's background scenery.

RelayPlanetH.Name: "RelayPlanetH" [Unused]
RelayPlanetH.Notes: A planet very similar to the metal planets in Gateway Galaxy. It has a place on one end for a cannon or a similar square-shaped object.

RelayPlanetI.Name: Gusty Garden -- Spiny Vines Planet
RelayPlanetI.Notes: The small planet with spiny vines used before Major Burrows' planet.

RepeartTimerSwitch.Name: Repeating Timer Switch
RepeartTimerSwitch.Notes: A timer switch that activates and deactivates something periodically.

RepeatBlock.Name: Snake Block
RepeatBlock.Notes: A set of blocks that move along a set path.

RepeatBlockLavaBoxPlanet.Name: Lava Lair -- Snake Block Planet
RepeatBlockLavaBoxPlanet.Notes: The planet where Snake Blocks appear in Bowser's Lava Lair.

RepeatBlockLavaBoxPlanetProminence.Name: Lava Lair -- Snake Blocks Planet Rotating Fire Balls
RepeatBlockLavaBoxPlanetProminence.Notes: A set of rotating fire balls used on the snake blocks planet in Bowser's Lava Lair.

RepeatBlockShadowChangeArea.Name: Snake Block Shadow Direction Area
RepeatBlockShadowChangeArea.Notes: An area that changes the direction for snake blocks.

RepeatTimerStageNormalStep.Name: Beat Block -- Large Platform
RepeatTimerStageNormalStep.Notes: A set of four solid purple blocks used in Beat Block Galaxy.

RepeatTimerStageStepA.Name: Beat Block -- Small Platform
RepeatTimerStageStepA.Notes: A single solid purple block used in Beat Block Galaxy.

RepeatTimerStageStepB.Name: Beat Block -- Long Platform
RepeatTimerStageStepB.Notes: A set of two solid purple blocks used in Beat Block Galaxy.

RestartCube.Name: Checkpoint Area [Cube]
RestartCube.Notes: An area that sets the next respawn point.

RestartObj.Name: Checkpoint Flag
RestartObj.Notes: A checkpoint flag used in several galaxies.

ReverseClipConveyerPlanet.Name: Haunty Halls -- Mattermouth Corridor Planet
ReverseClipConveyerPlanet.Notes: The corridor planet used at the end of the second mission of Haunty Halls Galaxy.

ReverseClipConveyorA.Name: Haunty Halls -- Moving Carpet A
ReverseClipConveyorA.Notes: A segment of a carpet platform used in Haunty Halls Galaxy.

ReverseClipConveyorB.Name: Haunty Halls -- Moving Carpet B
ReverseClipConveyorB.Notes: A segment of a carpet platform used in Haunty Halls Galaxy.

ReverseClipConveyorC.Name: Haunty Halls -- Moving Carpet C
ReverseClipConveyorC.Notes: A segment of a carpet platform used in Haunty Halls Galaxy.

ReverseFlowSandMoveStep.Name: Slipsand -- Metal Block
ReverseFlowSandMoveStep.Notes: A metal block platform used in the first mission of Slipsand Galaxy.

ReverseFlowSandPlanet.Name: Slipsand -- Cluckboom Planet
ReverseFlowSandPlanet.Notes: The second planet used in the first mission of Slipsand Galaxy.

ReverseGravity2DDossunPlanet.Name: Rightside Down -- Thwomps Planet
ReverseGravity2DDossunPlanet.Notes: The planet with the Thwomps used in Rightside Down Galaxy.

ReverseGravity2DLiftPlanet.Name: Rightside Down -- Slide Planet
ReverseGravity2DLiftPlanet.Notes: The section with the long slide from Rightside Down Galaxy.

ReverseGravity2DRoofActionPlanet.Name: Rightside Down -- Fire Flower Planet
ReverseGravity2DRoofActionPlanet.Notes: The planet where the Fire Flower is located in Rightside Down Galaxy.

ReverseGravity2DStartPlanetA.Name: Rightside Down -- Starting Section
ReverseGravity2DStartPlanetA.Notes: The first section of Rightside Down Galaxy.

ReverseGravityRoomPlanet.Name: Battlerock -- 2D Interior Section
ReverseGravityRoomPlanet.Notes: The large 2D interior section with gravity changing parts that is visited during the third mission.

ReverseGravityRoomPressGroundA.Name: Dreadnought -- Long Yellow Moving Piston
ReverseGravityRoomPressGroundA.Notes: A long yellow moving piston used in the 2D interior section.

ReverseGravityRoomPressGroundB.Name: Dreadnought -- Huge Yellow Moving Piston
ReverseGravityRoomPressGroundB.Notes: A huge yellow moving piston used in the 2D interior section.

ReverseGravityRoomPressGroundC.Name: Battlerock -- Small Yellow Moving Piston
ReverseGravityRoomPressGroundC.Notes: A small yellow moving piston used in the 2D interior section.

ReverseGravityRoomPressGroundD.Name: Battlerock -- Huge Yellow Moving Piston
ReverseGravityRoomPressGroundD.Notes: A huge yellow moving piston used in the 2D interior section.

ReverseGravityRoomPressGroundE.Name: Battlerock -- Small Red Moving Piston
ReverseGravityRoomPressGroundE.Notes: A small red moving piston used in the 2D interior section.

ReverseGravityTowerInside.Name: Good Egg -- Tower Planet Interior
ReverseGravityTowerInside.Notes: The inside section of the huge cylindrical tower planet.

ReverseGravityTowerPlanet.Name: Good Egg -- Tower Planet Exterior
ReverseGravityTowerPlanet.Notes: The outside section of the huge cylindrical tower planet.

ReverseKingdomPlanet.Name: Gold Leaf -- Main Planet
ReverseKingdomPlanet.Notes: The main planet that features some tall trees and a waterfall.

ReverseKingdomTreeA.Name: Gold Leaf -- Decorative Tree
ReverseKingdomTreeA.Notes: A decorative autumn tree used during the second and third missions.

RevolvingWay.Name: Pointer-Rotatable Cylinder [Unfinished]
RevolvingWay.Notes: An unfinished cylindrical object that the player can go through and rotate using the pointer.

RGTowerPressGroundA.Name: Good Egg -- Tower Planet Pusher
RGTowerPressGroundA.Notes: A pushing piston that appears inside the cylindrical tower planet.

RingBeamer.Name: Ring Beamer
RingBeamer.Notes: A yellow enemy with spikes on its head that periodically emits rings of electricity.

RingBeamerAreaObj.Name: Ring Beam Indicator
RingBeamerAreaObj.Notes: A ring used to indicate the size of the electric rings that a Sentry Beam fires off.

RingBeamerRushPlanet.Name: Dreadnought -- Blue Ring Beamer Planet
RingBeamerRushPlanet.Notes: A large blue planet with white lines and circles on the ground that indicate the radius of the Ring Beamer beams.

RisePictureBookPlanet.Name: Boo Moon -- Picture Book Planet
RisePictureBookPlanet.Notes: The folding planet used at the end of the first mission of Boo Moon Galaxy.

RoboRotateArmStep.Name: Boom Bunker -- Rotating Robot Arm
RoboRotateArmStep.Notes: A rotating robotic arm used on the starting planet of Bowser Jr.'s Boom Bunker.

RockBreakCage.Name: Small Purple Rock Mushroom Crystal
RockBreakCage.Notes: A small purple rock crystal used in Boulder Bowl Galaxy that can be destroyed with the Rock power-up.

RockBreakCageL.Name: Large Purple Rock Mushroom Crystal
RockBreakCageL.Notes: A large purple rock crystal used in Boulder Bowl Galaxy that can be destroyed with the Rock power-up.

RockCageS.Name: Tall Stone Rock
RockCageS.Notes: A tall stone rock that can be destroyed using the Rock power-up. Used in Boulder Bowl Galaxy.

RockCreator.Name: Large Boulder Spawner
RockCreator.Notes: A spawner for large rolling boulders.

RockPlanetOrbitSky.Name: Battlerock Sky
RockPlanetOrbitSky.Notes: The dark green sky model used in Battlerock Galaxy.

RockReflector.Name: Rock Mushroom Bounce Fence
RockReflector.Notes: A yellow fence that causes the player to bounce off from it if they roll into it with the Rock power-up.

RockRoadCircleA.Name: Honeyhive -- Bonus Room Rock Trails
RockRoadCircleA.Notes: A trail of a rolling rock used in the bonus rooms from Honeyhive Galaxy and Gold Leaf Galaxy.

RollingDrumPlanet.Name: Clockwork Ruins -- Rolling Wheels Planet
RollingDrumPlanet.Notes: The planet used at the end of the first mission of Clockwork Ruins Galaxy.

RollingOvalPlanet.Name: Battlerock -- Colorful Cannon Planet Base
RollingOvalPlanet.Notes: The yellow base for the cannon planet that features a hole for a cannon.

RollingOvalPlanetParts.Name: Battlerock -- Colorful Cannon Planet
RollingOvalPlanetParts.Notes: The colorful parts of the cannon planet from Battlerock Galaxy.

RollingWater.Name: Rolling Water Bubble
RollingWater.Notes: A rolling bubble of water; used in both Cosmic Cove Galaxy and Honeyhop Galaxy.

RollingWaterBreakArea.Name: Pop Rolling Water Bubble Area
RollingWaterBreakArea.Notes: An area that pops rolling water bubbles when they enter it.

Rosetta.Name: Rosalina
