TicoFatStarPiece.Name: Hungry Luma [World Map]
TicoFatStarPiece.Notes: A pink Luma that is hungry for Star Bits. Appears on the Starship Mario when requested on the World Map.

TicoGalaxy.Name: Hungry Luma [Galaxies]
TicoGalaxy.Notes: A pink Luma that is hungry for Star Bits and transforms into a portal to a galaxy accessible from the Comet Observatory.

TicoRail.Name: Moving Luma
TicoRail.Notes: A decorative Luma that moves on a path.

TicoReading.Name: Decorative Luma
TicoReading.Notes: A decorative Luma used in the cutscene of Rosalina reading to the Lumas in the Library.

TicoSeedGuidanceCube.Name: Hungry Luma Feeding Explanation Area [Cube]
TicoSeedGuidanceCube.Notes: An area which shows the player how to feed the Hungy Luma with Star Bits. This is useless in SMG2. The cube's origin is the base's center.

TicoShop.Name: Lumalee Shop [Mushrooms]
TicoShop.Notes: A large blue Luma that can transform on the spot into either a Life Mushroom or a 1-Up Mushroom after being paid some Star Bits.

TicoShopDice.Name: Lumalee Shop [Dices]
TicoShopDice.Notes: A blue Luma that can transform on the spot into a 1-Up Chance Cube.

TicoStarRing.Name: Trial Galaxies Guardian Luma
TicoStarRing.Notes: A Green Luma who transforms into a Green Launch Star upon player request.

TimeAttackClock.Name: Plus Clock
TimeAttackClock.Notes: A stopwatch that adds additional seconds to the Comet timer.

TimerCoinBlock.Name: Timed Coins ? Block
TimerCoinBlock.Notes: A ? Block that gives one Coin every time it is hit. Disappears after some hits and seconds.

TimerGravityChangeDrillRoom.Name: Flipsville -- Gravity-Changing Planet
TimerGravityChangeDrillRoom.Notes: The gravity-changing planet used in the second mission of Flipsville Galaxy.

TimerGravityChangeDrillRoomWall.Name: Flipsville -- Gravity-Changing Planet Panel
TimerGravityChangeDrillRoomWall.Notes: The back wall of the gravity-changing planet used in the second mission of Flipsville Galaxy.

TimerPieceBlock.Name: Timed Star Bits ? Block
TimerPieceBlock.Notes: A ? Block that gives one Star Bit every time it is hit. Disappears after some hits and seconds.

TimerSwitch.Name: Timer Switch
TimerSwitch.Notes: A switch that appears another switch after the requested number of frames elapsed.

TogeBegomanLauncher.Name: Spiky Topman Spawner
TogeBegomanLauncher.Notes: A black hole that spawns Spiky Topman. Defeated Spiky Topman will respawn after some time.

Togepin.Name: Pinhead
Togepin.Notes: A bowling pin that can be defeated using the Rock power-up.

TogepinAttackFoulArea.Name: Bowling Challenge Foul Area
TogepinAttackFoulArea.Notes: An area that, when entered, results in a foul during The Chimp's bowling challenge.

TogepinAttackMan.Name: The Chimp [Bowling Challenge]
TogepinAttackMan.Notes: The Chimp used for the bowling challenge in Melty Monster Galaxy.

TogepinScorer.Name: Bowling Challenge Controller
TogepinScorer.Notes: A controller that sets up bowling challenges and controls the scoring.

Togezo.Name: Spiny
Togezo.Notes: A red-shelled enemy with spikes on its back.

TombSpider.Name: Tarantox
TombSpider.Notes: The giant spider-like boss fought at the end of Space Junk Galaxy's third mission.

Tongari.Name: Spiny Hermit
Tongari.Notes: A white-shelled enemy with spikes on its back.

Tongari2D.Name: Spiny Hermit [2D]
Tongari2D.Notes: A variant of a Spiny Hermit for 2D sections.

Torpedo.Name: Torpedo Ted Spawner
Torpedo.Notes: A spawner for torpedo-like enemies that may home onto the player if they get in its range.

TowerModeCylinder.Name: Cylindrical 2D Movement Area [Cylinder]
TowerModeCylinder.Notes: An area that enforces 2D movement around a cylinder. Meant to be used for cylindrical-shaped planets. This area is always cylindrical

TrampleStar.Name: Pink Bouncy Ball Planet
TrampleStar.Notes: A small checkered red and pink planet which the player bounces on when stepped. It's primary apparition is in Ghostly Galaxy.

TransformFaceTicoBabyDemoObj.Name: Starship Mario Transformation Cutscene Object Holder
TransformFaceTicoBabyDemoObj.Notes: A holder that creates and registers some of the objects used for the cutscene where the Starship Mario is created.

TrapBaseA.Name: Tiny Gilded Metal Sphere
TrapBaseA.Notes: A tiny dark sphere of gilded metal used as a generic base for other objects such as Air Bubble generators, Bullet Bill launchers, flamethrowers, etc.

Trapeze.Name: Vine Swing
Trapeze.Notes: A swing made from vines that the player can swing across.

TreasureBoxBlueChip.Name: Treasure Chest with Blue Chip
TreasureBoxBlueChip.Notes: A brown treasure chest that reveals a Blue Chip when opened.

TreasureBoxCoin.Name: Treasure Chest with Coin
TreasureBoxCoin.Notes: A brown treasure chest that reveals a Coin when opened.

TreasureBoxCrackedAirBubble.Name: Cracked Treasure Chest with Air Bubble
TreasureBoxCrackedAirBubble.Notes: A gray treasure chest that reveals an Air Bubble when opened.

TreasureBoxCrackedBlueChip.Name: Cracked Treasure Chest with Blue Chip
TreasureBoxCrackedBlueChip.Notes: A gray treasure chest that reveals a Blue Chip when opened.

TreasureBoxCrackedCoin.Name: Cracked Treasure Chest with Coin
TreasureBoxCrackedCoin.Notes: A gray treasure chest that reveals a Coin when opened.

TreasureBoxCrackedEmpty.Name: Empty Cracked Treasure Chest
TreasureBoxCrackedEmpty.Notes: A gray treasure chest that reveals nothing when opened.

TreasureBoxCrackedKinokoLifeUp.Name: Cracked Treasure Chest with Life Mushroom
TreasureBoxCrackedKinokoLifeUp.Notes: A gray treasure chest that reveals a Life Mushroom when opened.

TreasureBoxCrackedKinokoOneUp.Name: Cracked Treasure Chest with 1-Up Mushroom
TreasureBoxCrackedKinokoOneUp.Notes: A gray treasure chest that reveals a 1-Up Mushroom when opened.

TreasureBoxCrackedPowerStar.Name: Cracked Treasure Chest with Power Star
TreasureBoxCrackedPowerStar.Notes: A gray treasure chest that reveals a Power Star when opened.

TreasureBoxCrackedYellowChip.Name: Cracked Treasure Chest with Star Chip
TreasureBoxCrackedYellowChip.Notes: A gray treasure chest that reveals a Star Chip when opened.

TreasureBoxEmpty.Name: Empty Treasure Chest
TreasureBoxEmpty.Notes: A brown treasure chest that reveals nothing when opened.

TreasureBoxGoldEmpty.Name: Empty Golden Treasure Chest
TreasureBoxGoldEmpty.Notes: A gold treasure chest that reveals nothing when opened.

TreasureBoxKinokoLifeUp.Name: Treasure Chest with Life Mushroom
TreasureBoxKinokoLifeUp.Notes: A brown treasure chest that reveals a Life Mushroom when opened.

TreasureBoxKinokoOneUp.Name: Treasure Chest with 1-Up Mushroom
TreasureBoxKinokoOneUp.Notes: A brown treasure chest that reveals a 1-Up Mushroom when opened.

TreasureBoxYellowChip.Name: Treasure Chest with Star Chip
TreasureBoxYellowChip.Notes: A brown treasure chest that reveals a Star Chip when opened.

TreasureSpot.Name: Coin Spot
TreasureSpot.Notes: A golden spot on the ground that reveals a Coin when it is hit with a Star Bit.

TreeCube.Name: Cubic Birch Tree [Broken]
TreeCube.Notes: A climbable birch tree with tall cubic leaves. This object usually crashes the game due to missing collision.

TrialBallPlanet.Name: Rolling Green -- Main Planet
TrialBallPlanet.Notes: The main and only planet of Rolling Green Galaxy.

TrialBubbleAPlanet.Name: Bubble Breeze -- Ending Section
TrialBubbleAPlanet.Notes: The second and final section of Bubble Breeze Galaxy's main planet.

TrialBubbleRevolvingPartsA.Name: Bubble Breeze -- Rotating Wood Log
TrialBubbleRevolvingPartsA.Notes: A large revolving wood log with two holes carved out of its sides.

TrialBubbleSPlanet.Name: Bubble Breeze -- Starting Section
TrialBubbleSPlanet.Notes: The colossal poison ocean planet and the first section of Bubble Breeze Galaxy.

TrialBubbleTimerMoveWallA.Name: Bubble Breeze -- Timed Moving Wooden Wall
TrialBubbleTimerMoveWallA.Notes: A wide wooden wall which moves on a timer.

TriangleTowerRailMoveStepSpring.Name: Chompworks -- Spring Tower Moving Platform
TriangleTowerRailMoveStepSpring.Notes: A gray moving platform used on the spring tower planet in Chompworks Galaxy.

TriangleTowerRotateStep.Name: Fluffy Bluff -- Cloud Tower Rotating Wood Gear
TriangleTowerRotateStep.Notes: A rotating wood gear used on the cloud tower planet in Fluffy Bluff Galaxy.

TriangleTowerRotateStepSpring.Name: Chompworks -- Spring Tower Rotating Metal Gear
TriangleTowerRotateStepSpring.Notes: A rotating metal gear used on the spring tower planet in Chompworks Galaxy.

TriangleTowerSpringPlanet.Name: Chompworks -- Spring Tower Planet
TriangleTowerSpringPlanet.Notes: The spring tower planet used in the second mission of Chompworks Galaxy.

TrickRabbit.Name: Escaping Star Bunny [With Paths]
TrickRabbit.Notes: The bunny from the minigames where the player has to catch it.

TrickRabbitFreeRun.Name: Escaping Star Bunny
TrickRabbitFreeRun.Notes: An escaping Star Bunny that runs around randomly without a path.

TrickRabbitFreeRunChild.Name: Escaping Star Bunny [Snow Cap]
TrickRabbitFreeRunChild.Notes: An individual escaping Star Bunny as seen in Snow Cap Galaxy that is spawned and controlled by a TrickRabbitFreeRunCollect object.

TrickRabbitFreeRunCollect.Name: Escaping Star Bunnies Controller
TrickRabbitFreeRunCollect.Notes: Sets up and controls the minigame where the player has to catch several escaping Star Bunnies (TrickRabbitFreeRunChild) under a time limit.

TrickRabbitGhost.Name: Invisible Escaping Star Bunny
TrickRabbitGhost.Notes: An unused variant of the escaping Star Bunny that turns invisible while it moves around. Requires a proper ObjNameTable entry in order to be used.

Tripod2Boss.Name: Megaleg [Duplicate]
Tripod2Boss.Notes: An exact copy of the normal TripodBoss model file. Usually crashes due to a missing file called Tripod2BossLegShadow.

TripodBoss.Name: Megaleg
TripodBoss.Notes: The massive robot boss fought on Bowser Jr.'s Robot Reactor that consists of many separate objects.

TripodBossBaseJointPosition.Name: Megaleg Joint Position
TripodBossBaseJointPosition.Notes: A marker object that specifies one of Megaleg's joint positions.

TriPodBossBodyA.Name: Megaleg Head
TriPodBossBodyA.Notes: Megaleg's head, the centerpiece of his body.

TripodBossBodyABloom.Name: Megaleg Head Glowing Arrows
TripodBossBodyABloom.Notes: The green/red glowing arrows on the sides of Megaleg's head.

TripodBossBottomKillerCannon.Name: Megaleg Bottom Bullet Bill Cannons
TripodBossBottomKillerCannon.Notes: The set of three Bullet Bill launchers on the underside of Megaleg's head.

TripodBossCoin.Name: Megaleg Coin
TripodBossCoin.Notes: A regular Coin that was intended to be used on Megaleg.

TripodBossCore.Name: Megaleg Grand Star Glass Cage
TripodBossCore.Notes: Megaleg's small glowing glass cage containing a Grand Star at the top of his head.

TripodBossEyeLight.Name: Megaleg Eye Light
TripodBossEyeLight.Notes: The pair of light beams coming out of Megaleg's eyes.

TripodBossEyeLightBloom.Name: Megaleg Eye Light Bloom
TripodBossEyeLightBloom.Notes: The actual bloom shader models for Megaleg's eye lights.

TripodBossFixParts.Name: Generic Fixed Megaleg Object [Unused]
TripodBossFixParts.Notes: A fixed segment for Megaleg that retrieves a proper model using ShapeModelNo. However, no more models exist for this object.

TripodBossFoot.Name: Megaleg Foot
TripodBossFoot.Notes: A large player-crushing mechanical foot belonging to Megaleg.

TripodBossFootBloom.Name: Megaleg Foot Glowing Arrows
TripodBossFootBloom.Notes: The green/red glowing arrows on Megaleg's feet.

TriPodBossGearA.Name: Megaleg Black Gear
TriPodBossGearA.Notes: A black mechanical gear composing part of Megaleg's thighs.

TriPodBossGearB.Name: Megaleg Brown Gear
TriPodBossGearB.Notes: A brown mechanical gear composing part of Megaleg's thighs.

TriPodBossGearBody.Name: Megaleg Main Gear
TriPodBossGearBody.Notes: A large mechanical gear used at the center of Megaleg's head underside.

TriPodBossGearC.Name: Megaleg Gray Gear
TriPodBossGearC.Notes: A gray mechanical gear composing part of Megaleg's thighs.

TriPodBossGearSmallA.Name: Megaleg Small Yellow Gear
TriPodBossGearSmallA.Notes: A small yellow mechanical gear composing part of Megaleg's legs.

TriPodBossGearSmallB.Name: Megaleg Small Gray Gear
TriPodBossGearSmallB.Notes: A small gray mechanical gear composing part of Megaleg's legs.

TriPodBossGearSmallC.Name: Megaleg Long Brown Gear
TriPodBossGearSmallC.Notes: A long brown mechanical gear composing part of Megaleg's thighs and legs.

TripodBossGuardWall.Name: Megaleg Grand Star Fence
TripodBossGuardWall.Notes: A circular metal grid fence consisting of breakable and self-regenerating segments which Megaleg activates on phase 2 to defend the Grand Star.

TripodBossKillerGenerater.Name: Megaleg Bullet Bill Launcher
TripodBossKillerGenerater.Notes: A temporarily destroyable Bullet Bill launcher that is used on Megaleg's legs.

TripodBossKinokoOneUp.Name: Megaleg 1-Up Mushroom
TripodBossKinokoOneUp.Notes: A special 1-Up Mushroom that is attached to one of Megaleg's body parts.

TriPodBossLeg1A.Name: Megaleg Hip Joint
TriPodBossLeg1A.Notes: The metal cylinder which connects Megaleg's hip joint connectors to his head.

TriPodBossLeg1B.Name: Megaleg Hip Connector Piece
TriPodBossLeg1B.Notes: The small slightly sloped metal piece connecting Megaleg's hip joints to his thigh gears.

TriPodBossLeg1C.Name: Megaleg Knee Connector Piece
TriPodBossLeg1C.Notes: The small metal piece which connects Megaleg's knee joint to his thigh gears.

TriPodBossLeg2A.Name: Megaleg Shin & Knee
TriPodBossLeg2A.Notes: The lower half of Megaleg's leg, up to and including the knee joint.

TriPodBossLeg2ABloom.Name: Megaleg Shin Glowing Arrows
TriPodBossLeg2ABloom.Notes: The green/red glowing arrows on Megaleg's leg parts.

TriPodBossLeg3A.Name: Megaleg Ankle
TriPodBossLeg3A.Notes: The small metal bar which connects Megaleg's feet and leg.

TriPodBossLeg3B.Name: Megaleg Ankle Connector Piece [Unfinished]
TriPodBossLeg3B.Notes: An unfinished segment that would have connected the foot and the short ankle piece.

TriPodBossLeg3C.Name: Megaleg Foot [Unfinished]
TriPodBossLeg3C.Notes: A textureless unfinished early version of a Megaleg foot.

TriPodBossLegBottom.Name: Megaleg Foot Bottom
TriPodBossLegBottom.Notes: The bottom side of a Megaleg foot.

TripodBossRailMoveParts.Name: Generic Moving Megaleg Object [Unused]
TripodBossRailMoveParts.Notes: A path-moving segment for Megaleg that retrieves a proper model using ShapeModelNo. However, no more models exist for this object.

TripodBossRotateParts.Name: Generic Rotating Megaleg Object [Unused]
TripodBossRotateParts.Notes: A rotating segment for Megaleg that retrieves a proper model using ShapeModelNo. However, no more models exist for this object.

TripodBossShell.Name: Megaleg Grand Star Cage
TripodBossShell.Notes: The big metal cage seen at the top of Megaleg's head.

TripodBossStepPoint.Name: Megaleg Stepping Point
TripodBossStepPoint.Notes: A marker object which specifies one of several stepping points for one of Megaleg's legs.

TripodBossStepStartArea.Name: Move Megaleg Leg Area [Sphere]
TripodBossStepStartArea.Notes: An area that causes Megaleg's specified leg to move once entered.

TripodBossUnderKillerCannon.Name: Megaleg Lower Head Bullet Bill Cannons
TripodBossUnderKillerCannon.Notes: The lower row of six Bullet Bill launchers on Megaleg's head.

TripodBossUpperKillerCannon.Name: Megaleg Upper Head Bullet Bill Cannons
TripodBossUpperKillerCannon.Notes: The upper row of seven Bullet Bill launchers on Megaleg's head.

TripodPlanet.Name: Robot Reactor -- Megaleg Planet
TripodPlanet.Notes: The planet where Megaleg is fought in Bowser Jr.'s Robot Reactor.

TropicalCloudTowerPlanet.Name: Starshine Beach -- Main Planet
TropicalCloudTowerPlanet.Notes: The sandy beach planet used in Starshine Beach.

TShapePlanet.Name: Space Junk -- T-Shaped Planet
TShapePlanet.Notes: A futuristic-style metal planet with a tridimensional T-shape.

Tsukidashikun.Name: Bomp
Tsukidashikun.Notes: A gray rectangular stone with a face that pushes objects in front of it.

TsukidashikunBig.Name: Large Bomp [Unfinished]
TsukidashikunBig.Notes: An unfinished large version of the Bomp, but the model is still visually the same size as the regular one, leading to visually weird collision.

TubeColorsA.Name: Rolling Masterpiece -- Decorative Paint Tubes A
TubeColorsA.Notes: A set of paint tubes used in the background of Rolling Masterpiece Galaxy.

TubeColorsB.Name: Rolling Masterpiece -- Decorative Paint Tubes B
TubeColorsB.Notes: A set of paint tubes used in the background of Rolling Masterpiece Galaxy.

TubedRelayPlanet.Name: Honeyhive -- Tree Trunk Tube Planet
TubedRelayPlanet.Notes: A planet with a cut hollow tree trunk going through the middle.

TubeSlider.Name: Slider Controller
TubeSlider.Notes: Sets up the tubular slide sections along a set path. It also creates several special "TubeSlider"-related objects that are connected to it.

TubeSliderCoinCreator.Name: Slider Coin Group
TubeSliderCoinCreator.Notes: A group of Coins that appear during slide sections.

TubeSliderCoinCreatorPurple.Name: Slider Purple Coin Group
TubeSliderCoinCreatorPurple.Notes: A group of Purple Coins that appear during slide sections.

TubeSliderCourceSnow.Name: Freezy Flake -- Snow Slide
TubeSliderCourceSnow.Notes: The snowy slide used in the first mission of Freezy Flake Galaxy.

TubeSliderCourse.Name: Tall Trunk -- Wood Slide
TubeSliderCourse.Notes: The wooden slide used in the second mission of Tall Trunk Galaxy.

TubeSliderCrystal.Name: Slider Crystal [Broken]
TubeSliderCrystal.Notes: A destroyable crystal intended to be used on sliders. Model files have been removed. Therefore, the object is useless.

TubeSliderDamageObj.Name: Slider Spiky Plant Group
TubeSliderDamageObj.Notes: A group of Spiky Plants that is used on the wooden slide in Tall Trunk Galaxy.

TubeSliderEnemy.Name: Slider Spiny
TubeSliderEnemy.Notes: A variant of a Spiny that is used on the wooden slide in Tall Trunk Galaxy.

TubeSliderGoalPlanet.Name: Tall Trunk -- Slide Goal Planet
TubeSliderGoalPlanet.Notes: The planet used at the end of the slide in Tall Trunk Galaxy.

TubeSliderHana.Name: Slider Wiggler
TubeSliderHana.Notes: A variant of a Wiggler that is used on the wooden slide in Tall Trunk Galaxy.

TubeSliderJumpStep.Name: Slider Trampoline [Broken]
TubeSliderJumpStep.Notes: An object that causes the player to jump. It was intended to be used on sliders. Model files have been removed. Therefore, the object is useless.

TubeSliderStartPlanet.Name: Tall Trunk -- Slide Start Planet
TubeSliderStartPlanet.Notes: The planet where the wooden slide starts in Tall Trunk Galaxy.

TubeSliderTicoCoin.Name: Slider Comet Medal
TubeSliderTicoCoin.Notes: A variant of the Comet Medal item that is intended to be used in slider sections.

TurtleBeamKameck.Name: Koopa Shell Magikoopa
TurtleBeamKameck.Notes: A Magikoopa that casts Koopa Shells.

TwilightAir.Name: Twilight Atmosphere
TwilightAir.Notes: The unusual red atmosphere used in Bubble Breeze Galaxy.

TwinFallLakePlanet.Name: Beach Bowl -- Twin Falls Planet
TwinFallLakePlanet.Notes: A pair of two planets with big lakes that are connected by a series of waterfalls and grass platforms. The upper planet features some snowy islands surrounded by an icy mountain range.

TwinFallLakeWaterFall.Name: Beach Bowl Twin Falls Waterfall Effect
TwinFallLakeWaterFall.Notes: A waterfall splash effect that is used on the Twin Falls planet in Beach Bowl Galaxy.

TwinPeanutsPlanetA.Name: Gusty Garden -- Long Rolling Rocks Planet
TwinPeanutsPlanetA.Notes: A long curved beady planet with dirt trails.

TwinPeanutsPlanetB.Name: "PeanutPlanet" [Duplicate]
TwinPeanutsPlanetB.Notes: An exact duplicate of the unused PeanutPlanet.

TwisterSan.Name: Galactic Tornado
TwisterSan.Notes: A large tornado enemy with a wide attraction range.

TwisterSanSlim.Name: Slim Galactic Tornado
TwisterSanSlim.Notes: A slim tornado enemy with a somewhat wide attraction range.

TwoLegs.Name: Digga-Leg
TwoLegs.Notes: The boss fought at the end of the first mission of Spin-Dig Galaxy.

TwoLegsBullet.Name: Digga [Digga-Leg]
TwoLegsBullet.Notes: A variant of the Digga enemy that appears during the fight against Digga-Leg in Spin-Dig Galaxy.

TwoLegsPlanet.Name: Spin Dig -- Digga-Leg Planet
TwoLegsPlanet.Notes: The planet where Digga-Leg is fought in Spin-Dig Galaxy.

UFOBattleStageC.Name: Battlerock -- UFO with Square Slot
UFOBattleStageC.Notes: A metallic UFO with a square slot at the center of one side.

UFOBattleStageD.Name: Battlerock -- UFO with Columns
UFOBattleStageD.Notes: A big metallic UFO with four small columns on one side.

UFOBlueStarCupsule.Name: Pull Star UFO Platform
UFOBlueStarCupsule.Notes: A UFO platform with a usable Pull Star inside the glass capsule on the top side.

UFOKinoko.Name: Starshroom
UFOKinoko.Notes: A spaceship in the shape of a Toad head.

UFOKinokoLanding.Name: Landed Starshroom
UFOKinokoLanding.Notes: A landed spaceship in the shape of a Toad head.

UFOKinokoLandingAstro.Name: Landed Starshroom [No Interior]
UFOKinokoLandingAstro.Notes: A variant of UFOKinokoLanding with no interior and opaque windows that is used in Grand Finale Galaxy.

UFOKinokoLandingBlackSmoke.Name: Crashed Starshroom Smoke Effect
UFOKinokoLandingBlackSmoke.Notes: An effect for the smoke coming out of a crashed Starshroom.

UFOKinokoUnderConstruction.Name: Comet Observatory -- Starshroom
UFOKinokoUnderConstruction.Notes: This object represents all the construction stages of the Starshroom seen in the Garage, including the finished one, and picks the stage to load based on the current savefile's progress.

UFONormalB.Name: Dreadnought -- Bullet UFO
UFONormalB.Notes: A metallic bullet-shaped platform which can be broken by an explosion.

UFONormalD.Name: Battlerock -- Breakable UFO Platform
UFONormalD.Notes: A variant of UFOStrongA that can be destroyed by an explosion.

UFOSandObstacleA.Name: Dusty Dune -- Long Sand Brick Block
UFOSandObstacleA.Notes: A long block of sand bricks.

UFOSandObstacleAEffect.Name: Dusty Dune -- Long Sand Brick Block Effect
UFOSandObstacleAEffect.Notes: Dust cloud particles that are used for a tall object sinking into or emerging from sand. Primarily meant for use with UFOSandObstacleA.

UFOSandObstacleB.Name: Dusty Dune -- Sand Brick Block
UFOSandObstacleB.Notes: A cubic block of sand bricks.

UFOSandObstacleBEffect.Name: Dusty Dune -- Sand Brick Block Effect
UFOSandObstacleBEffect.Notes: Dust cloud particles that are used for a cubic object sinking into or emerging from sand. Primarily meant for use with UFOSandObstacleB.

UFOSandObstacleC.Name: Dusty Dune -- Slim Sand Brick Block
UFOSandObstacleC.Notes: A slim block of sand bricks.

UFOSandObstacleCEffect.Name: Dusty Dune -- Slim Sand Brick Block Effect
UFOSandObstacleCEffect.Notes: Dust cloud particles that are used for a thin object sinking into or emerging from sand. Primarily meant for use with UFOSandObstacleC.

UFOShapePassThroughPlanet.Name: Sky Station -- Starting Planet
UFOShapePassThroughPlanet.Notes: The planet used at the start of Sky Station Galaxy.

UFOShapePassThroughPlanetParts.Name: Sky Station -- Starting Planet Log Cover
UFOShapePassThroughPlanetParts.Notes: A log that covers the holes of the starting planet in Sky Station Galaxy.

UFOShapePlanetWanwanRoute.Name: Sky Station -- Starting Planet Chomp Trails
UFOShapePlanetWanwanRoute.Notes: The Chain Chomps trails used on the starting planet of Sky Station Galaxy.

UFOStrongA.Name: Battlerock -- Generic UFO Platform
UFOStrongA.Notes: A metallic UFO platform that is used in Battlerock Galaxy.

Unbaba.Name: Magmaargh
Unbaba.Notes: A large lava enemy that tries to eat the player.

UnbabaSlim.Name: Magmaw
UnbabaSlim.Notes: A smaller version of a Magmaargh.

UnderGroundDangeonPlanetA.Name: Slimy Spring -- Snoodle Section
UnderGroundDangeonPlanetA.Notes: The first half of Slimy Spring Galaxy that consists of the starting cave and the underwater tunnels with Snoodles.

UnderGroundDangeonPlanetB.Name: Slimy Spring -- Underwater Boo Planet
UnderGroundDangeonPlanetB.Notes: The second half of Slimy Spring Galaxy that features a lot of Underwater Boos and the goal section.

UnderseaTunnelPlanet.Name: Bigmouth -- Main Planet
UnderseaTunnelPlanet.Notes: The massive fish-shaped main planet from Bigmouth Galaxy.

UniverseAir.Name: Starry Atmosphere
UniverseAir.Notes: A starry atmosphere that appears during Bowser Jr.'s Fiery Flotilla's boss fight.

Unizo.Name: Sea Urchin
Unizo.Notes: A purple Urchin with spikes on its body; intended for water areas.

UnizoLand.Name: Land Urchin
UnizoLand.Notes: A red furry Urchin with spikes on its body; intended for land areas.

UnizoLauncher.Name: Land Urchin Spawner
UnizoLauncher.Notes: A point that periodically spawns several Land Urchins.

UnizoShoal.Name: Shoal Urchin
UnizoShoal.Notes: A purple Urchin with spikes on its body. It doesn't create any water splash particles when it moves.

ValveSwitch.Name: Valve Switch
ValveSwitch.Notes: A screw-like green valve that the player can spin on top of to bring it up or down to activate a switch.

ViewGroupCtrlArea.Name: View Group Area
ViewGroupCtrlArea.Notes: When entered by the player, all compatible objects in its ViewGroup will be forced to render.

ViewGroupCtrlCube.Name: View Group Area [Cube]
ViewGroupCtrlCube.Notes: When entered by the player, all compatible objects in its ViewGroup will be forced to render. The cube's origin is the base's center.

VRDarkSpace.Name: Boss Blitz Sky
VRDarkSpace.Notes: The sky model used in Sling Pod Galaxy, Bowser Jr.'s Lava Reactor and Boss Blitz Galaxy.

VROrbit.Name: Good Egg Sky
VROrbit.Notes: The iconic sky model from Super Mario Galaxy.

VRSandwichSun.Name: Melty Molten Sky
VRSandwichSun.Notes: The sky model used in Melty Molten Galaxy.

VR_GrandGalaxy.Name: Grand World Map Atmosphere
VR_GrandGalaxy.Notes: The atmosphere used on the Grand World Map.

VsBegomanSpikePlanet.Name: Dreadnought -- Trapped Luma Planet
VsBegomanSpikePlanet.Notes: A planet from Dreadnought Galaxy with lots of colored patches and small towers.

VsBoomerangBrosPlanet.Name: Boom Bunker -- Hammer Bros. Planet
VsBoomerangBrosPlanet.Notes: The second planet used in Bowser Jr.'s Boom Bunker.

VsBossJugemAir.Name: Thunderstorm Atmosphere
VsBossJugemAir.Notes: The thunderstorm atmosphere used during the Giga-Lakitu battle in Yoshi Star Galaxy.

VsKingTossinPlanet.Name: Boulder Bowl -- Rollodillo Planet
VsKingTossinPlanet.Notes: The planet where Rollodillo is fought in Boulder Bowl Galaxy.

VsKoopaLv3Sky.Name: Galaxy Generator Sky
VsKoopaLv3Sky.Notes: The sky model used in Bowser's Galaxy Generator.

VsOtaRockTankIcePlanet.Name: Shiverburn -- Prince Pikante Planet
VsOtaRockTankIcePlanet.Notes: The planet where Prince Pikante is fought in Shiverburn Galaxy.

VsOtaRockTankIcePlanetFence.Name: Shiverburn -- Prince Pikante Planet Fence
VsOtaRockTankIcePlanetFence.Notes: The fence that surrounds the Prince Pikante planet in Shiverburn Galaxy.
